
<entry done=TRUE uid=521314>T-shirt
<lex>
<sen uid=521313  tag=teesh>
<gr>nc</gr>
<field>Clothing</field>
<def>a short-sleeved round-necked buttonless cotton garment for the upper body, forming a T-shape when spread out flat, and usually carrying a design or slogan </def>
<ex>&ellip. badges and T-shirts proclaiming opposition to the Central Electricity
Generating Board's plan to build a pressurised water reactor on the Somerset
coast.
<clues hidden=TRUE>=</clues></ex>
<ex>London's trendiest people are making a show of slopping around in jeans and
T-shirts, sweatpants and trainers. </ex>
<ex>He was wearing a Megadeath T-shirt, extremely thick glasses and a broad
grin.</ex></sen></lex></entry>

<entry done=TRUE uid=521330>hair shirt
<lex>
<sen uid=521312  tag=hairsh>
<gr>nc</gr>
<def>a shirt made of haircloth, worn as a sign of penitence or self-denial; usually in extended use</def>
